2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper considers the transmission over time-varying binary erasure channels, which is a common scenario in mobile wireless networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the design and optimization of a communication system, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
4. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly deal with cryptography or security, but the use of error-correcting codes is relevant to secure communication. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - The paper does not seem to have any direct relevance to computers and society.
